cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  A Mathlib-free Lean 4 Formalization of MV-algebras and the
  Soundness of Łukasiewicz / Basic Logic
message: >-
  If you use this software or build on the proofs, please cite it
  using the metadata below.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Claude, Opus Models Family"
  - family-names: Alekseev
    given-names: Anton
repository-code: "https://github.com/alexeyev/lukasiewicz-many-valued-logic-lean"
abstract: >-
  A from-scratch formalization, in pure Lean 4 core with no Mathlib
  dependency, of MV-algebras (via Chang's axioms) and the proof
  systems for Łukasiewicz logic and Hájek's Basic Logic (BL). On the
  logical side it includes a complete algebraic soundness proof for
  all eleven BL axioms over arbitrary MV-algebras (including the
  prelinearity axiom a6, proved equationally via Mundici's
  Propositions 1.6 and 1.7), the BL+dn vs Łukasiewicz basis
  equivalence (axioms L1-L4), and the Local Deduction Theorem. On
  the algebraic side it develops the structure theory of
  Cignoli-Mundici Chapter 1 (Propositions 1.5-1.11, Lemmas
  1.2-1.9, the Boolean center, and the MV-algebra metric),
  homomorphisms and ideals with the ideal-congruence
  correspondence, the quotient MV-algebra, and the full suite of
  isomorphism theorems — First, Second, Third, the Correspondence
  (Lattice) Theorem, and the Chinese Remainder Theorem — together
  with the lattice of ideals. Every result depends on at most the
  standard `propext` and `Quot.sound` axioms; none depends on
  `sorryAx` or `Classical.choice`, so the entire development is
  complete and choice-free.
keywords:
  - Lean 4
  - formal verification
  - interactive theorem proving
  - MV-algebras
  - Łukasiewicz logic
  - Basic Logic
  - many-valued logic
  - fuzzy logic
  - mathematical logic
  - ideals
  - quotient algebras
  - isomorphism theorems
  - Chinese Remainder Theorem
license: Beerware
version: "1.0.0"
date-released: "2026-06-18"
